{"id": "295", "instruction": "What is the result of expanding the determinant $D \\!=\\! \\left| \\begin{array} {c c c c} {{{1}}} & {{{0}}} & {{{-1}}} & {{{-1}}} \\\\ {{{0}}} & {{{-1}}} & {{{-1}}} & {{{1}}} \\\\ {{{-1}}} & {{{-1}}} & {{{1}}} & {{{0}}} \\\\ {{{a}}} & {{{b}}} & {{{c}}} & {{{d}}} \\\\ \\end{array} \\right|$ by the fourth row?\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\n- 2 a+b-2 c-d\n$$\nB. $$\n- 3 a+2b-2 c-d\n$$\nC. $$\n- a+b-2 c-d\n$$\nD. $$\n- 3 a-b-2 c-d\n$$\nE. $$\n- 3 a+b-2 c-d\n$$\nF. $$\n- 3 a+b+2 c-d\n$$\nG. $$\n- 3 a+b- c-d\n$$\nH. $$\n- 3 a+b-2 c-2d\n$$\nI. $$\n3 a+b-2 c-d\n$$\nJ. $$\n- 3 a+b-2 c+d\n$$", "output": "E"}
